{% extends 'layout.njk' %}

{% set pageTitle = 'Guidance' %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-width-container govuk-body">
    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
      <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <span class="govuk-caption-xl">Guidance</span>
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Help to enter multiple volumes or readings into a return</h1>

        <p class="gem-c-lead-paragraph">You can enter multiple values into a return by copying and pasting from a document on your device. For example, from an Excel spreadsheet or a text file.</p>

        <p>If you're using a spreadsheet, each of the values should be in one column. They should be in date order.</p>

        <figure class="guidance-no-left-margin">
          <image src="/assets/images/example-excel-01-min.png" width="300px"></image>
          <figcaption class="govuk-!-font-size-16 guidance-caption-width">Example 1: an Excel spreadsheet with 2 columns, one for dates and one for volumes or readings.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p>Select and then copy the values column. You do not need the dates.</p>

        <figure class="guidance-no-left-margin">
          <image src="/assets/images/example-excel-02-min.png" width="300px"></image>
          <figcaption class="govuk-!-font-size-16 guidance-caption-width">Example 2: an Excel spreadsheet with the values column selected.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p>Paste the values into the box on the form. The values will appear in a column.</p>

        <figure class="guidance-no-left-margin">
          <image src="/assets/images/example-input-01-min.png" width="500px"></image>
          <figcaption class="govuk-!-font-size-16 guidance-caption-width">Example 3: how readings or volumes look after being pasted into the box.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p>For this form to work, values should:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>either be on separate lines or be separated by a comma</li>
          <li>cover the entire return period - if a value is missing, use an <span class="guidance-example-code"><code>x</code></span> to fill the gap</li>
          <li>run sequentially to match the return period dates</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
